Class Student

java.lang.Object
Student
public class Student extends Object
The Student class implements various methods for unique ID storage, manipulation, and validation. This class also implements a way to get an Answer from a Student given a Question
Version:
1.0
Author:
George Matta

      The unique ID of the Student

    • usedIDs

      private static Set<String> usedIDs
      A static Set of the IDs already in the system We use a HashSet because of its constant-time access (since we're only checking if an ID is contained in the set) and its unique elements

      A final static field of the length of an ID. This implementation uses 7

      public void setID(String generatedID)

    • findValidID

      private static String findValidID()
      A static method to find a valid ID. This method repeatedly, randomly, generates an ID until it finds one not in use
      Returns:
      The generated user ID (guaranteed to be unique)

    • generateRandomID

      private static String generateRandomID()
      A static method to generate a random ID This method generates an alphanumeric, case-sensitive, `ID_LENGTH` character long ID.
      Returns:
      The generated user ID (not guaranteed to be unique)
